<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-04-10T09:32:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-04-10T09:32:00-05:00" n="289" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d289">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">824.51/179: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cottrell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">La
                                        Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-04-10T10:00:00-04:32"><hi rend="italic">April 10,
                                        1923—10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 2:20
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>21. Referring to my cable of April 3, noon. The President has named Jorge
                            Saenz, Manager of the Bank of the Nation, and José <pb facs="0561" n="445" xml:id="pg_445"/> Mendieta, Manager of the National Bank, a
                            Commission with full powers to go to New York to arrange modifications
                            in loan contract. They leave April 26th.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cottrell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>